<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,405,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
Comparing the 
<typeStatus box="[326,424,405,431]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fisher" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[462,585,406,431]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[462,585,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">D. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[600,702,405,432]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Figs 6–8</figureCitation>
), as well as other specimens of this species, with a 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1374,405,431]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">B. concisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[253,384,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Figs 13–15</figureCitation>
), photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[617,715,441,467]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">holotype</typeStatus>
and original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chemsak, Linsley &amp; Noguera" authorityYear="1992" box="[1032,1161,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[1032,1161,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">D. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1178,1309,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–70" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1604,1628]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,249,1578]" captionTargetId="figure-52@23.[151,1436,237,1581]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 65–70. Bebelis spp. 65–66) Dorcasta modesta Belon, 1903, holotype: 65) Dorsal habitus; 66) Labels. 67–68) Dorcasta laetabilis Belon, 1903, holotype: 67) Labels; 68) Dorsal habitus. 69) Dorcasta zeteki Fisher, 1947, holotype, dorsal habitus (by Jesus Santiago Moure). 70) Adetus elongatus Lameere, 1893, holotype, dorsal habitus (by Jesus Santiago Moure)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886434/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Figs 65–66</figureCitation>
), I was not able to find a reliable difference between these three nominal species. The size in specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fisher" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[1231,1410,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1231,1410,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Bebelis angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very variable. Although in general they are larger than in specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2006" box="[932,1047,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concisa">
<emphasis box="[932,1047,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">B. concisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are specimens with the same length. Accordingly, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2006" box="[386,503,550,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concisa">
<emphasis box="[386,503,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">B. concisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fisher" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[557,677,550,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[557,677,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">B. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chemsak, Linsley &amp; Noguera" authorityYear="1992" box="[938,1062,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[938,1062,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">B. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
